> And maybe wait for #17403 before merging this

I agree. In the meantime, I have untangled the imports because of the `large-import` label and also because I think it is reasonable that `ResidueField` does not import `ClosedImmersion` but rather the other way round.
Please merge master and incorporate the new changes. Thanks!

LGTM other than these minor comments
But I think I wrote most of the statements so I'll refrain from maintainer-merging.

Thanks!

bors merge

Pull request successfully merged into master.

Build succeeded:
  * [Lint style](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/11420338174/job/31775923816)
  * [Build](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/11420338174/job/31775923764)
And maybe wait for #17403 before merging this

```suggestion
lemma Hom.Spec_map_residueFieldMap_fromSpecResidueField (x : X) :
```
Or is this too long?
Is it hard to make this into an iff?
No, done.
This moved to a new file, right?
No longer after implementing Andrews suggestion.
I think this can go into `ResidueField` along with `SpecToEquivOfField`.

Not sure, this depends on the `IsClosedImmersion` instance of `Spec.map (X.residue x)` and we can't import `IsClosedImmersion` in `ResidueField`. The alternative would be to add `IsPreimmersion (Spec.map (X.residue x))` in `ResidueField` separately and only later upgrade it to `IsClosedImmersion`, but not sure if this is really better than the current version.
I feel that the latter makes more sense to me. As this result itself has little to do with closed immersions.
Okay, I did that and added a comment on the `IsPreimmersion` instance to find the stronger result.
Is this still necessary?
Indeed, it is not.

```suggestion
lemma range_fromSpecResidueField (x : X.carrier) :
```
